      transliteration: 'tad ity anabhisandhāya phalaṁ yajña-tapaḥ-kriyāḥ\ndāna-kriyāś ca vividhāḥ kriyante mokṣa-kāṅkṣibhiḥ',
      translation: 'With Tat — without aiming at the fruit — the various acts of sacrifice, austerity, and giving are performed by seekers of liberation.',
